fix: convert markdown tables to code blocks in feishu post messages

Root cause: _build_outbound_payload forced 'text' msg_type when tables
were detected, causing:
- Path A (fatal): first send 'post', later content has table -> edit
  sends msg_type='post' with text payload -> API 230001 -> edit broken
- Path B (ugly): first send 'text', table rendered as raw | chars

Fix:
1. _convert_tables_to_code_blocks(): replace complete markdown table
   blocks with ```-fenced code blocks
2. _build_outbound_payload(): detect tables -> convert to code blocks
   -> return 'post' type (preserving bold/lists/code block rendering)
3. consumer.py safety net: on edit failure fallback to send_message,
   re-enable editing for the new message instead of permanently
   disabling it

Tests: 13 -> 19 (6 new table conversion tests), all pass